You are helping build Atlas, an AI-powered career readiness web app.

Product scope:
- Authenticated users submit one resume and one target job description.
- Atlas generates a saved readiness dashboard, resume improvement suggestions, and personalized 30/60/90-day roadmap quests.
- Users can mark roadmap quests complete or incomplete.
- Atlas can show professional milestone badges computed from completed quest categories.
- Ask Atlas is available only after the first analysis and uses the current report, structured resume evidence, quest progress, and RAG context.
- v1 excludes payments, LinkedIn scraping, job-board integrations, automated applications, and hiring guarantees.
- v1 excludes streaks, XP economy, leaderboards, competitive leagues, push notifications, mascot-led nudges, daily lessons, and generic curriculum paths.

Stack:
- Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind in apps/web.
- Product modules live in apps/web/src/modules: public-site, auth, career-dashboard, analysis-workbench, readiness-report, roadmap, ask-atlas, reports.
- Shared app infrastructure lives in apps/web/src/core: auth, supabase, ai, rag, validation.
- Supabase Auth, Postgres, RLS, and pgvector.
- OpenAI gpt-4o-mini for generation.
- OpenAI text-embedding-3-small for curated career guidance embeddings.
- FastAPI + Docling for PDF/DOCX resume extraction.

Engineering standards:
- Keep AI logic, prompt construction, RAG retrieval, and secret usage server-side.
- Never expose OpenAI keys or Supabase service-role keys in client code.
- Validate user inputs before extraction, retrieval, or generation.
- Validate AI output before rendering or saving.
- Add tests for validation, prompt construction, output schema handling, RAG chunking, retrieval filtering, and document file validation.
- Keep document extraction separate from report generation.
- Keep RAG ingestion separate from private user resume processing.
- Keep Python RAG as offline/admin ingestion only; runtime retrieval belongs in apps/web/src/core/rag.
- Use Supabase RLS for every user-owned table.
- Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks.

Privacy standards:
- Do not store uploaded resume files.
- Do not store full raw resume text.
- Store structured resume evidence only when saved Ask Atlas needs resume context.
- Do not embed private resumes, job descriptions, reports, or Ask Atlas messages into the shared RAG knowledge base.
- Do not log private resume or job description content.

Design standards:
- Public nav: Home, Use Cases, Privacy, FAQ, About, Login, Sign up for free.
- Build the usable authenticated dashboard first, not a marketing-only landing page.
- Use the Atlas name and tagline: "Map your next career move."
- Use a clean professional interface with white or soft gray surfaces, restrained blue accents, thin borders, and 6-12px radius components.
- Do not overpromise employment outcomes.
- Login page copy: "Welcome back" and "Continue your career roadmap."
- Signup page copy: "Start mapping your next career move" and a short note that accounts save reports, quests, and Ask Atlas chats.
